    <h2>3rd ERCOFTAC "Machine learning for fluid dynamics" workshop</h2>
    <p>
		The workshop invites abstract submissions on any aspect of Machine Learning applied to Fluid Dynamics problems. These include, but are not limited to:

		<ul>
			<li> Data-driven/data-augmented models (e.g., rheology, turbulence modeling, combustion, multiphase, ...); </li>
			<li> ML-assisted reduced-order modelling or surrogate modeling of flows, feature detection, signal processing; </li>
			<li> ML-based flow control or optimization; </li>
			<li> Super-resolution reconstruction of flow fields; </li>
			<li> Uncertainty quantification; </li>
			<li> ML-accelerated flow solvers. </li>
		</ul>

		Whenever possible, the authors are encouraged to use the workshop test cases to demonstrate their proposed approaches. However, this is not mandatory, and different test cases will be accepted.
    </p>

